spin
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:2
Definition:a run of luck; a chance, a go, esp. good, bad, fair, rough spin (from spinning a coin)
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1949 Havelock During the rationing we didn't get a fair spin from our grocer as far as `short' things went.
